    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. One factor (Test conditions, Gradation 2 vs. required 3) is below threshold but accepted by the team on the basis that ASTM F1717 mandates a single standardized test condition and no alternative protocol exists. Overall credibility is sufficient for a Medium model risk, Medium assurance level COU. Validation results support FEA model acceptance for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending prediction.",
